      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The humanitarian arguments, though rooted in moral obligations, can be effectively countered by acknowledging that the US has a sovereign duty to protect its citizens and maintain national stability. By framing the debate in terms of competing values, the opposing side can argue that the US must prioritize its own security and economic interests, which are essential to fulfilling its moral obligations to the vulnerable. This approach recognizes that the US cannot effectively protect the rights of all individuals if it is unable to protect itself.",
